xdot (1.2-2-maruska) unstable; urgency=medium

  [ Jose.R.Fonseca ]
  * Fix clicks.
  * Fix clicks again.
  * Fix ellipses.
  * Simple example.
  * Cleanup xdot parser.
  * Separate widget from window.
  * Use signals.
  * Jump between nodes and edges.
  * Add copyright header.
  * Convert tabs to spaces.
  * Fix return value on error.
  * Adapt for pydot-1.0.2.
  * Require pydot version 0.9.10.
  * Remove trailing whitespace.
  * Set executable flag.
  * Fix HSV color parsing.
  * Fix HSV color parsing to support space-separated values as well as comma-separated ones.
  * Show unrecognized colors on stderr and use white instead of crashing.
  * Properly support HSV colors (floats can start with a '.').
  * When positioning the text vertically, use the coordinate for the baseline rather than absolute bottom of the text.  Unfortunately I couldn't figure out how to determine the descent of a font used by pango.Layout.
  * Make text fit in boxes.
  * Remove pointless move_to.
  * Filled shapes are always outlined in dot (unless you specify the same color for the outline and the inside).
  * Scale descender too.
  * Handle line widths.
  * Support dashing.
  * Handle style="solid".
  * Ignore invalid colors instead of assuming white.
  * Animate scrolling when you click on a node/edge.
  * Zoom out while moving a large distance.
  * Stop the animation if I start clicking or dragging the mouse.
  * Never zoom in during animation.
  * Fix unit mismatch in comparison.
  * Distinguish clicks from drags.
  * I wonder if there's a better solution?
  * Ctrl-dragging zooms.
  * Fix space conversion formula.
  * Avoid division by zero.
  * Shift-dragging zooms an area.
  * Escape or a different mouse button aborts the current drag action.
  * Change the cursor when you're over a jump point.
  * Highlight the node under mouse.
  * Highlight all kinds of objects.
  * Associate nodes to edges.
  * Highlight the destination of the edge too.
  * Gentler highlight color.
  * Add an open command to the toolbar.
  * Add error dialogs when a file cannot be parsed.
  * Show the file name in the window title.
  * Fix error dialog title.
  * Add some margin to zoom to fit.
  * Zoom-to-fit on open.
  * Make zoom-to-fit sticky.
  * Allow to specify the graphviz filter.
  * Fix library usage broken due to the global options.
  * Handle polylines. Handle ports in nodes.
  * Import pyparsing-1.5.0.
  * Fix error handling when you open an invalid file.
  * Make mouse wheel zoom around the mouse cursor rather than center of window.
  * Replace pydot and pyparsing by a much faster hand written lexer and parser.
  * Ignore empty bb attribute inside subgraphs.
  * Show an error message dialog when failing to open the input file.
  * Check for unicode (from Jaap Karssenberg).
  * Check subprocess returncode (by Jaap Karssenberg).
  * Support filled bezier shape.
  * Workaround broken pangocairo bindings.
  * Begin to separate the xdot attribute parsing from the handling code.
  * Fix typo.
  * Fix another typo.
  * Fix typo (arpad.zsuzsi).
  * Fix yet another typo.
  * Fix filled ellipses.
  * Parse subgraphs correctly.
  * Reloads the file on the 'r' key (based on peterbjorgensen's patch).
  * Accept floating bounding box (by Krzysztof.Goj).
  * Add setup script (Marius Gedminas, issue #19).
  * Add support for ColorBrewer Color Schemes.
  * Automatically reloads open file when it changes (Robert Meerman).
  * Use gobject.timeout_add.
  * Properly handle motion-notify-event (from lodatom).
  * Add reload button.

